            . I am a book-keeper at Axminster, to 
               <persName id="t18130714-12-person167">
                  Robert 
                  Russell
               <interp inst="t18130714-12-person167" type="surname" value="Russell"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18130714-12-person167" type="given" value="Robert"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18130714-12-person167" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            's waggon. I saw the tub of butter put in the waggon. This is my book where I entered it, it was on the 24th of May, 1813; it was marked N. B. No. 1745; this is the farmer's iron that marked it: I helped to load the waggon myself.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18130714-12-person168">
                  JOHN 
